The paper deals with modeling and analyzing complex datasets with entities of different types and relationships, which is a common problem in social networks, data mining, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the efficiency and versatility of the proposed approach, which suggests that it could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
